{"title":"Fizik’s new top-of-the-range Vega Carbon shoes use a wider last for added comfort","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/fizik-vega-carbon-shoes","date":1747839600000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/fizik-vega-carbon-shoes\">Fizik’s new top-of-the-range Vega Carbon shoes use a wider last for added comfort</a></p>\n\n<p>Fizik has launched the £389.99 Vega Carbon, a new pro-level shoe for racing, which replaces the previous top spec Vento Stabilita.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The brand says the new shoe improves foot comfort thanks to a 1.5mm wider fit. It also dispenses with the lasting board that’s a feature of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-cycling-shoes\">best cycling shoes</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-970x970.webp\" alt=\"Fizik Vega Carbon shoes\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-970x970.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-300x300.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-150x150.webp 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-768x768.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-1536x1536.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-2048x2048.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-75x75.webp 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-350x350.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-750x750.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_5_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-1140x1140.webp 1140w\" /><figcaption>Fizik</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Peek under the insole of pretty much any pair of shoes, whether designed for cycling or other use, and you’ll see a flat layer of cardboard. This is the lasting board and is used to hold the pieces of the shoe together when it’s assembled.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Vega Carbon does away with this, with the upper bonded directly to the carbon outsole. Although Fizik says that there’s minimal weight loss, the integrated outsole does reduce stack height and is also claimed to make the shoe stiffer, torsionally more rigid and improve support under the midfoot.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+6\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Subs-flash-164-for-web-6-970x300.webp\" alt=\"Cyclist banner saying 'escape to your favourite place every month', click here to subscribe'\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Subs-flash-164-for-web-6-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Subs-flash-164-for-web-6-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Subs-flash-164-for-web-6-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Subs-flash-164-for-web-6-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Subs-flash-164-for-web-6-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Subs-flash-164-for-web-6-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Subs-flash-164-for-web-6-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Revised fit</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-970x970.webp\" alt=\"Fizik Vega Carbon shoes\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-970x970.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-300x300.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-150x150.webp 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-768x768.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-1536x1536.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-2048x2048.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-75x75.webp 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-350x350.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-750x750.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/VER1DMR1C2090_6_fizik-vento-vega-carbon-white-yellow-fluo-shoes-1140x1140.webp 1140w\" /><figcaption>Fizik</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Fizik says that it has also updated its shoe’s shape in response to changes in riders’ <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-to-be-aerodynamic-cycling\">body position</a> and bike fit, along with the trend to fit cleats further back on the shoe’s sole than in the past.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The shoe’s axis has been made straighter and there’s also a reduced drop from the heel to the toe and increased arch support, which Fizik says improves foot stability and pedalling efficiency, as well as increasing midfoot leverage on the pedals.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The toe box has also been widened, which it claims improves foot comfort. Fizik isn’t the only brand to move to a wider last for its shoes. Other brands to do so include Specialized, which has increased the width of the toebox in its latest <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/specialized-torch-3-0-shoes-review\">Torch 3.0</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/specialized-s-works-ares-2-shoes\">Ares 2 shoes</a>. It’s not the first to remove the lasting board either, with the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/shimano-s-phyre-rc903-shoes-review\">Shimano RC903 </a>and some of Pearl Izumi’s shoes also examples of cycling shoes made without one.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fizik has used a new fabric, called Aeroweave Pro, which it says improves on its previous generation Aeroweave upper by adding more resilience and weather resistance and reducing stretch, while still offering high breathability. There are mesh sections around the toes and sides of the upper to increase ventilation and reduce pressure on the foot.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The shoe is closed with two Boa Li2 dials, which are lower profile than its previous IP1 dial, while there’s no tongue, improving upper comfort.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/fizik-helmets\">Fizik releases its first helmets, including two road, one TT and one MTB</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/fizik-saddles-insider\">Best seat in the house: behind the scenes at Fizik</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-cycling-shoes\">Best road cycling shoes 2025 reviewed and rated</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tutorials/how-to-fit-and-adjust-cleats-for-cycling-shoes\">Watch: How to fit and adjust cleats for cycling shoes</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Fizik Vega Carbon weights and prices</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-970x647.webp\" alt=\"Fizik Vega Carbon shoes\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-1536x1025.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/fizik_vega_6-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>Fizik</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Fizik claims a weight of 239g per shoe in an unspecified size, plus another 20g for the insole. That’s not super-lightweight, but still competitive. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Vega Carbon shoe is available in sizes from 36 to 48, with half sizes from 37 to 47. There are two colours on offer: white and the white/yellow fluoro used by the Movistar team. It’s priced at £389.99 / $469.99 / €390.00.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-4-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"Cyclist newsletter banner saying 'get your regular dose of Cyclist, click here to sign up'\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-4-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-4-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-4-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-4-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-4-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-4-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-4-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/fizik-vega-carbon-shoes\">Fizik’s new top-of-the-range Vega Carbon shoes use a wider last for added comfort</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Pnorman","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"2215892a965af8a437cb193492406a7e39625f20627cec38c28439925a7638ef","category":"Cycling"}